post_text:
As we look forward to another Longhorn Football season we are hoping to accommodate as many happy fans as possible. We are also committed to following local and state COVID-19 guidelines to ensure every fan is safe.

Because of these guidelines we are offering more seating options to allowing for people to feel more comfortable while social distancing. We are going to allow fans to bring lawn chairs and enjoy the game seated on the track. Only fans with chairs will be permitted on the track. Fans wishing to stand and watch the game must stand behind the track and watch from there.

Additionally, there will be no fan interaction with players before, during, or after the game. Upon completion of the game all spectators, families(other than those providing transportation for student athletes), etc. are asked to promptly leave the facility.

Thank you for your continued support of all Longhorn athletic programs in these difficult times! Longhorn Spirit! Longhorn Pride!

-Coach Hayes

post_text:
Summer Workouts Begin Monday June 8th!!!

When: Mon-Thursday 6:00-8:00pm all summer
Where: Forestburg School gym / weight room
Who: Incoming 7th graders-Seniors (boys & girls)

What to bring: Bring your own water bottle, athletic clothing, athletic shoes, and cleats (boys only)

What to expect: Summer workouts are a combination of weight workouts, cardio workouts, agility and flexibility work, as well as sport-specific instruction for football, volleyball, and basketball.

Important notes:
Incoming 7th graders and anyone who did not play a sport for Forestburg ISD last year will need to bring a completed physical from a doctor before participating in summer workouts.

post_text:
Wednesday nights until we return to school we will have the stadium lights on between 8:00 PM and 9:00 PM. When you see the lights please say a prayer for the safety of our students, staff, and community. Our hearts go out to all of our students but especially to our seniors as they are being denied a great life experience! We love our students and our staff and this is a small way that we can show we are thinking of them. As you see the lights, please be in prayer for our community as a whole. We hope that all of Forestburg is safe from all health concerns. We are also thinking about those who may have lost jobs or whose bottom lines have been greatly affected and we are hoping for a quick recovery!

But most importantly please allow the lights to be a symbol that this situation will end soon. Let us be the “light” to the world, high upon a lofty hilltop! Together we will get through it! Longhorn Pride!

post_text: Parents, we need your help. Please have conversations with your students about the dangers of participating in "games" that cause a person to pass out. We have addressed the issue at school, but we want you to be informed about this as well. The newest fad is to push on a student's chest until the student is no longer able to catch his/her breath and passes out, which results in a brain rush when the student regains consciousness. Any students participating in this at school will be immediately placed in ISS. Thank you for reinforcing this message at home.
text: Parents, we need your help. Please have conversations with your students about the dangers of participating in "games" that cause a person to pass out. We have addressed the issue at school, but we want you to be informed about this as well. The newest fad is to push on a student's chest until the student is no longer able to catch his/her breath and passes out, which results in a brain rush when the student regains consciousness. Any students participating in this at school will be immediately placed in ISS. Thank you for reinforcing this message at home.

2019 Forestburg Longhorns Varsity Football Playoff Shirts are now on sale!!! The front and back design pictured in this post will be featured on a white long sleeve performance t-shirt.

Cost will be $25 per shirt (cash or check)

Available sizes include Youth Medium and Youth Large, as well as all Adult sizes XS through 4XL.

Orders must be turned in to Coach Cumby or the school office and must be paid for by noon on Saturday 11/9/2019.

Order forms are available in the school office and will also be available at the home football games this Friday.

If you have any questions, please email Coach Cumby at trey.cumby@forestburgisd.net

post_text:
Seeking Volunteers:

We are looking for one more person to run the chain crew at home football games this season. Chain crew members will receive free entry into the game, a free meal from the concession stand, and a Longhorn Chain Crew T-Shirt.

We also need one person to run the clock for junior high home football games. This person will receive free admission and a free meal from the concession stand.

Please respond to this post if you are interested in volunteering for either of these positions. Thanks!

Mark your calendars now Forestburg Homecoming is Friday, September 20th against Denton Calvary.

Monday, 9-16: Put a Cap on the Lions! (Wear a regular or silly hat)
Tuesday, 9-17: Make the Lions See Double!(Dress like a Twin)
Wednesday, 9-18: Hunt the Lions! (Wear Camo)
Thursday, 9-19: Say Yee-Yee to the Lions! (Dress like a Redneck)
Friday, 9-20: Show your Longhorn Spirit! (Wear Maroon, Gold & White)

post_text:
As football season approaches there are some key dates all players and parents should be aware of:

Wednesday July 31st - Parent/Player meeting with coaches in the school cafeteria from 6:00 pm - 7:00 pm (Junior High and Varsity)

Monday August 5th - First day of Two-a-Days. Practice every week day at the football field from 7:00 am - 9:00 am. Weights every week day from 6:00 pm - 7:00 pm. (Varsity)

Friday August 9th - Midnight Madness Intra-squad scrimmage beginning at midnight on Friday night / Saturday morning (Varsity)

Saturday August 10th - Watermelon Festival Parade with Athletics Float. Meeting time TBD (Varsity)

Wednesday August 14th - Last day of Two-a-Days (Varsity)

Friday August 16th - Scrimmage at home vs Lone Star North beginning at 7:30 pm (Varsity)
